# Design Token System

This project uses a **3-layer design token architecture**. All colors, spacing,
and typography values must come from this system — never use hardcoded values.

---

## Token Layers

### Layer 1 — Primitives (`src/styles/theme.css`)
Raw palette values. **Never reference these in components.**
They exist only to be consumed by semantic tokens.

```css
/* ✅ Correct — used only inside globals.css */
--color-brand-primary: var(--primitive-orange-500);

/* ❌ Wrong — primitives used directly in a component */
<div className="bg-[var(--primitive-orange-500)]">
```

### Layer 2 — Semantic tokens (`src/app/globals.css`)
Intent-based names. **Always use these in components.**

### Layer 3 — Tailwind utilities (generated from @theme)
Tailwind utility classes are auto-generated from semantic tokens.
**These are what you write in JSX.**

