## Rules

### ❌ Never Do This
```tsx
/* Hardcoded hex */
<div className="text-[#FF6E28] bg-[#202124]" />

/* Arbitrary CSS variable (primitive) */
<div className="text-[var(--primitive-orange-500)]" />

/* Hardcoded color in tailwind.config */
brand: { orange: "#FF6E28" }   // ← wrong, put in theme.css
```

### ✅ Always Do This
```tsx
/* Semantic Tailwind class */
<div className="text-brand-primary bg-text-primary" />

/* Or CSS variable (semantic) in className */
<div style={{ color: "var(--color-brand-primary)" }} />
```

---

## Adding a New Token

1. **Add the raw hex** to `src/styles/theme.css` under the appropriate palette group
2. **Create a semantic token** in `src/app/globals.css` `:root` block
3. **Register in `@theme`** block in `globals.css`
4. **Add to `tailwind.config.ts`** so the Tailwind class is available
5. **Document it** in `docs/Design_systems.md`

---

## Focus Ring Standard

All interactive elements must use the brand focus ring:
```tsx
className="focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-[var(--color-brand-primary)] focus-visible:outline-none"
```
